sentences: Ronnie Singer (June 9, 1928 – September 12, 1953) was an American jazz guitarist from Chicago.

Ronnie Singer (June 9, 1928 – September 12, 1953) was an American jazz guitarist from Chicago. Singer was influential on other jazz musicians, and was considered "just as good as Jimmy Raney", according to Jimmy Gourley who played with both guitarists in Chicago.
At the age of 25, he and his wife committed suicide together in a hotel room in New York City.
